"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-10-celine-dion-to-perform-at-paris-2024-olympics-opening-ceremony\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Famous Canadian singer Celine Dion is set to perform at the 2024 Paris Olympics amid battle with Stiff Person Syndrome, SPS.  Other singers to perform include Dua Lipa and Aya Nakamura.  The Olympics will commence on Friday, July 26, 2024, ending on August 11, 2024, in Paris, France.  According to guardian.ng, the 2024 edition is estimated to have over 600,000 spectators in attendance and will be broadcast to 80 giant screens in public places.  For the first time in history, this year opening ceremony, directed by Thomas Jolly, will be held outside an Olympics stadium.  The game is held every four years.  DAILY POST recalls thatCeline Dion made her first public appearancein recent times at the 2024 Grammy Awards ceremony.    Burna Boy headlines 2024 SummerJam Festival in Germany [VIDEO]  Young Jonn flaunts photos with Davido's cousin amid relationship rumours  I do not know Celine Dion - Arsenal star, Bukayo Saka  US Election: I did not permit Trump to use my song for his campaign - Celine Dion clarifies  'I will be remembered for my classics even if I stop singing' - Celine Dion  'I am honoured' - Celine Dion relishes comeback performance at Paris Olympics opening ceremony  Celine Dion performs at 2024 Paris Olympics amid health battle [VIDEO]  Celine Dion charges $2m to perform one song at Olympic ceremony  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"